<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="127" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,512,1439]" pageId="14" pageNumber="127">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,512,539]" pageId="14" pageNumber="127">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Cercus ventrally with numerous black, thick spines including ca. four long, inner marginal ones (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="15.[151,250,1871,1896]" captionTargetBox="[162,1425,561,1852]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[162,1425,561,1852]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 9. Hirtodrosophila zouae sp. nov. (A−M: holotype 06468). A, B, periphallic organs (posterior and posterolateral view, respectively); C, ventral lobe of epandrium (lateral view); D, cerci (ventral view); E, dorsal part of surstylus (posterolateral view); F, inner surface of surstylus (posterolateral view); G, H, 10th sternite (anterior and dorsal view, respectively); I−K, phallic organs (ventral, ventrolateral, and lateral view, respectively); L, aedeagus and sensilla of paramere (ventral view); M, aedeagus (lateral view; red arrows point at lateral process and ventral small projections)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3415697" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3415697/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="127">Fig. 9D</figureCitation>
). Aedeagus apically with large membranous process which tapering distally in lateral view, subapically swollen dorsally, with a pair of lateral processes, with a pair of lateral processes and a series of small acute projections ventrally (
<figureCitation box="[266,332,621,647]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="15.[151,250,1871,1896]" captionTargetBox="[162,1425,561,1852]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[162,1425,561,1852]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 9. Hirtodrosophila zouae sp. nov. (A−M: holotype 06468). A, B, periphallic organs (posterior and posterolateral view, respectively); C, ventral lobe of epandrium (lateral view); D, cerci (ventral view); E, dorsal part of surstylus (posterolateral view); F, inner surface of surstylus (posterolateral view); G, H, 10th sternite (anterior and dorsal view, respectively); I−K, phallic organs (ventral, ventrolateral, and lateral view, respectively); L, aedeagus and sensilla of paramere (ventral view); M, aedeagus (lateral view; red arrows point at lateral process and ventral small projections)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3415697" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3415697/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="127">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
I–M); lateral processes small, flat, finely serrate on dorsal margin (
<figureCitation box="[1080,1230,621,647]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="15.[151,250,1871,1896]" captionTargetBox="[162,1425,561,1852]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[162,1425,561,1852]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 9. Hirtodrosophila zouae sp. nov. (A−M: holotype 06468). A, B, periphallic organs (posterior and posterolateral view, respectively); C, ventral lobe of epandrium (lateral view); D, cerci (ventral view); E, dorsal part of surstylus (posterolateral view); F, inner surface of surstylus (posterolateral view); G, H, 10th sternite (anterior and dorsal view, respectively); I−K, phallic organs (ventral, ventrolateral, and lateral view, respectively); L, aedeagus and sensilla of paramere (ventral view); M, aedeagus (lateral view; red arrows point at lateral process and ventral small projections)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3415697" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3415697/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="127">
Fig. 
<date box="[1133,1158,621,647]" pageId="14" pageNumber="127">9I</date>
, L, M
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="127" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,512,1439]" pageId="14" pageNumber="127">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,337,656,683]" pageId="14" pageNumber="127">Description</emphasis>
(characters commonly seen in 
<taxonomicName authority="Chen &amp; Katoh &amp; Gao, 2019" authorityName="Chen &amp; Katoh &amp; Gao" authorityYear="2019" box="[695,823,657,683]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Hirtodrosophila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="127" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zhangae" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[695,823,657,683]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="127">H. zhangae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[832,923,657,683]" pageId="14" pageNumber="127">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[832,923,657,683]" pageId="14" pageNumber="127" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
not repeated) (
<specimenCount box="[1099,1122,657,683]" pageId="14" pageNumber="127" type="male">♂</specimenCount>
). Head (
<figureCitation box="[1220,1341,657,683]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1923,1948]" captionTargetBox="[232,1355,166,1904]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[232,1355,166,1904]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 3. Left lateral habitus, head and thorax (dorsal view), wing (left ventral or right dorsal view), and abdomen (dorsal view). A−D, H. zhangae sp. nov. (holotype 06470); E−H, H. zouae sp. nov. (holotype 06468); I−L, H. nigrispina sp. nov. (holotype 06472)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3253624/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="127">Figs 3E, F</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1354,1367,656,683]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1609,1634]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,849,1589]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1436,849,1589]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 5. Head (anterior view), postocciput (posterior view), cibarium (dorsal and lateral view), and prementum (ventral and lateral view). A−F, H. zhangae sp. nov. (holotype 06474); G−L, H. zouae sp. nov. (holotype 06471); M−R, H. nigrispina sp. nov. (paratype 06473)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3415691" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3415691/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="127">5</figureCitation>
G–L): Gena yellowish brown to brown, anteriorly dark brown. First flagellomere grayish yellow; arista with five dorsal branches. Supracervical setae 13–16 per side; postocular setae 26–29 per side. Cibarium with ca. seven medial and ca. 18 posterior sensilla per side.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,512,1439]" pageId="14" pageNumber="127">
Thorax (
<figureCitation box="[295,412,801,827]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1923,1948]" captionTargetBox="[232,1355,166,1904]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[232,1355,166,1904]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 3. Left lateral habitus, head and thorax (dorsal view), wing (left ventral or right dorsal view), and abdomen (dorsal view). A−D, H. zhangae sp. nov. (holotype 06470); E−H, H. zouae sp. nov. (holotype 06468); I−L, H. nigrispina sp. nov. (holotype 06472)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3253624/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="127">Fig. 3E, F</figureCitation>
): Postpronotal lobe yellowish brown. Mesonotum yellowish brown to brown; stripes sometimes very indistinct.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,512,1439]" pageId="14" pageNumber="127">
Male terminalia (
<figureCitation box="[395,466,873,899]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="15.[151,250,1871,1896]" captionTargetBox="[162,1425,561,1852]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[162,1425,561,1852]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 9. Hirtodrosophila zouae sp. nov. (A−M: holotype 06468). A, B, periphallic organs (posterior and posterolateral view, respectively); C, ventral lobe of epandrium (lateral view); D, cerci (ventral view); E, dorsal part of surstylus (posterolateral view); F, inner surface of surstylus (posterolateral view); G, H, 10th sternite (anterior and dorsal view, respectively); I−K, phallic organs (ventral, ventrolateral, and lateral view, respectively); L, aedeagus and sensilla of paramere (ventral view); M, aedeagus (lateral view; red arrows point at lateral process and ventral small projections)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3415697" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3415697/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="127">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
): Epandrium with ca. 38 long setae per side. Cercus with ca. 36 long setae. Surstylus ventrally tapered with upper row of ca. eight prensisetae, and lower row of 7−8 prensisetae; inner surface with ca. 24 long setae; anterior margin with ca. seven short setulae. Paramere apically with ca. five minute sensilla. Aedeagal apodeme slightly curved, about 1/2 length of aedeagus.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,512,1439]" pageId="14" pageNumber="127">
